    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "He that walketh in his uprightness feareth the LORD: but {he that is} perverse in his ways despiseth him.",
    "hash": "afa37ea2c97e71c78b3055c609968af0293b588abb1cbcd2d1e084625916e02f"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.14.3",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "In the mouth of the foolish {is} a rod of pride: but the lips of the wise shall preserve them.",
    "hash": "800e46982f70b461d9861ec1ab715e4e77cad668f15b26e5277037887a033c77"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.14.4",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "Where no oxen {are}, the crib {is} clean: but much increase {is} by the strength of the ox.",
